{"id":"6107","name":"bright-early-rough-around-the-edges-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Rough Around The Edges Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2010-11-23T11:00:00-06:00","tags":["army corps of engineers","bankruptcy","black friday","cool springs galleria","extreme makeover","fisk university","georgia o&apos;keefe","hate crimes","hazel o&apos;leary","lighthouse christian school","mnpd","nashville flood","opry mills","prepaid tuition program","second harvest food bank","thanksgiving"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/andrewchelton/3857874824/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3507/3857874824_78b3568b8a.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Good morning, Nashville. It&#x2019;s been a few weeks since we&#x2019;ve checked in with Fisk University, which was teetering on the edge of bankruptcy and trying to sell off its Georgia O&#x2019;Keefe art collection to pay the bills. <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101122/NEWS04/11220322/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">The university is now trying to come up with a way to raise $90 million by reaching out to alumni and community donors, hosting some musical events and awarding an honorary degree to &#x201C;someone who [Fisk President Hazel O&apos;Leary] promises will delight the students.&#x201D;</a> Fisk has seen numerous students drop out for financial reasons in addition to an overall decline in enrollment numbers which means less money flowing into the school.</p><ul><li><strong>Hate crimes on the decline.</strong> <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101123/NEWS03/11230327/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Nashville&#x2019;s hate crimes were reduced by almost a third in 2009, which is the first time in five years that the numbers have declined</a>. Metro Police attribute this to Nashvillians becoming more educated and more sensitive to crimes like that.</li><li><strong>Gettin&#x2019; hangry. </strong>If you&#x2019;ve got some extra cash or food this season, <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=13553103\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Second Harvest Food Bank really needs our help</a>. Donations are down 15%, there&#x2019;s more folks in need than ever, so please send them some love.</li><li><strong>Seriously? Seriously. </strong>To everyone who has landed on this site by furiously googling Opry Mills Black Friday deals, there are none (well, except <a href=\"http://www.basspro.com/homepage.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.basspro.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">these guys</a>)! Because <a href=\"http://www.wbir.com/news/article/144034/2/Opry-Mills-to-remain-closed-during-lawsuit\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wbir.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Opry Mills is closed</a>. <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101123/WILLIAMSON01/11230308/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Try your luck at the Cool Springs Galleria</a>.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces.</strong> The Army Corps of Engineers is <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/25890187/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">releasing another report on how they handled the May flood</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101123/NEWS04/11230329/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Tennessee is ending their prepaid tuition program</a> because they say it has cost taxpayers millions of dollars &#x2026; We&#x2019;re looking at a <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2010/11/morning-storms-thanksgiving-storms/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">potentially stormy Thanksgiving</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=13550550\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Classes were held at Lighthouse Christian School yesterday for the first time since the flood</a>. Lighthouse was the recipient of a pretty fancy renovation by <em>Extreme Makeover: Home Edition.</em></li></ul><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/andrewchelton/3857874824/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Andrew Chelton</a>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/09/14/happy-hour-the-neverending-story/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Happy Hour: The Neverending Story\">Happy Hour: The Neverending Story</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/11/26/calling-all-crazy-people-opry-mills-midnight-madness-black-friday/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Calling All Crazy People: Opry Mills Midnight Madness [Black Friday]\">Calling All Crazy People: Opry Mills Midnight Madness [Black Friday]</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}